<@U0770P4SKEH> How do I enable direct messages to my slack bot (currently I have to @ the bot but I want to be able to direct message it)

To enable direct messaging to your Slack bot, follow these steps:

1. Click on your workspace name in the top left corner of Slack. 

2. Select "Administration" from the dropdown menu, then "Manage Apps".

3. This will open the "App Directory", find your app in the list and click on it.

4. In the "App Settings" panel, click on "Bot Users".

5. Under "Bot Users", make sure the button for "Always Show My Bot as Online" is in the 'on' position.

After these steps are complete, you should be able to locate your bot in the list of available direct messages. Simply click on the bot's name when you want to message it directly, the same way you would with any other user. If you were not able to find your bot in the list, you might need to invite your bot into your workspace. Go the Apps section in the main channel, and invite your bot.

Let me know if you need more help!
